Assignment 1         //file name starts with ASS1

1. Write an 8086 Assembly Language Program to subtract two 8-bit signed integers. The
  numbers can be stored in data segment.

2. Write an 8086 Assembly Language Program to print your name as a string. Name can be
  stored in the data segment as a string.

3. Write an 8086 Assembly Language Program to reverse a string using stack and display
  the result.

4. Write an 8086 Assembly Language Program which will ask for a number and the no. will
  be taken from keyboard. Print the number in decimal, binary and hexadecimal format.

5. Now modify the program in Q2 so that it will ask for your name and takes the input from
  key board.
